  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2287",
  "title": "Pagination Widget autoHideContainer does not hide the entire element.",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nA Bug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nWhen no results returned, `autoHideContainer` on the Pagination widget doesn't hide the entire element. \r\n\r\nYou can view this behaviour here by searching for something with no results: https://jsfiddle.net/gmattucc/qxhpm91j/\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nThat the entire pagination element is hidden like the behaviour of other widgets.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nAll\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\nHave the data react root have `display=none` like all the other widgets.\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nv2.0.2\r\n",
